Preparatory Committee for Celebrating Feb. 16 Formed in Mongolia 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- An inaugural ceremony of the preparatory committee of the Mongolia-Korea Friendship Society for celebrating February 16 was held at the Mongolian Palace of Culture on Jan. 11.
 On display there were photos showing the Songun leadership exploits performed by leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The executive chairman of the society said in a speech that   Kim Jong Il is a great statesman who is making a new history of the cause of independence by pursuing independent politics and the Songun policy. The friendship society will widely introduce his greatness among the Mongolian people, the executive chairman added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ch. Surenjav, chairman of the society, was elected chairman of the preparatory committee at the ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The preparatory committee set a celebration period from Jan. 12 to Feb. 16 and decided to hold colorful events including meetings and art performances at the units named after the three generals of Mt. Paektu and contribute special write-ups and programs to media in this period.

Japan's Vicious Moves against Chongryon under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- One of hideous crimes Japan has committed against the Korean people after the liberation of Korea is that it has pursued vicious hostile policy toward the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon), says Rodong Sinmun Thursday in a signed article.
 Referring to violence, violent language, arson, murder and other crimes the Japanese reactionaries committed against Chongryon and Koreans in Japan, the article continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Violence cases against Korean students in Japan have steadily increased after the adoption of the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration.
 Violent language, violence and threatening cases against students of Korean schools numbered 319 from September 2002 to January 2003.
 Such acts have been committed all the more viciously against Chongryon and institutions under it. Seizure and financial expropriation of institutions including the Central Standing Committee of Chongryon have been undisguised and business activities of Korean traders and industrialists have been seriously infringed upon at the instigation of the Japanese government and under its direct intervention. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Worse still, the Japanese reactionaries tried to totally destroy Chongryon while hatching a plot to use even the "Self-Defence Forces" in case of emergency after defining Chongryon as a target of the law on the prevention of destructive activities, the law which is applicable to anti-state plot-breeding organizations or spy groups. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese government has put media in motion to create hostile atmosphere toward the DPRK, Chongryon and Koreans in Japanese society and put Koreans in Japan in fear and panic so that they can hardly live at ease. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chongryon is a sacred overseas Koreans' organization of the DPRK and a legitimate body. It has so far conducted patriotic activities to defend the dignity and right of the Korean nation and has done nothing contrary to the Japanese law. The organization has played the role of a diplomatic mission for friendship between the Korean and the Japanese people because they have no diplomatic relations. The Japanese government is legally and morally liable to ensure Chongryon's activities and protect Koreans in Japan even in view of the content of the organization's activities and mission and international human rights norms. The Japanese government, however, has persecuted Chongryon and restricted its activities under this or that pretext, regarding it as a thorn in the flesh. It even shut its eyes to the Right hooligans' reckless terrorism against Chongryon and instigated them to do it.
 Japan's persistent suppression and persecution of Chongryon and Koreans in Japan instead of apologizing and compensating for hideous crimes it has committed against the Koreans in the past is little short of adding another crime to its previous crimes.

Art Performance Given by Art Squad of Youth League 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- An art performance was given by the art squad of the Central Committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League at the Central Youth Hall on Jan. 18 to celebrate the 60th anniversary of the youth league.
 The performance began with chorus "Our Father Is Marshal  Kim Jong Il". The performers put on the stage narration and song "The Eternal Smile", male vocal solo "The General Is the Son of Guerrillas", solo story-telling "Thinking of the General" and female vocal solo "Arirang on Pass Chol" which represent the young people's deep reverence and praise of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also put on the stage mixed duet "Pride of Youth", brass ensemble and chorus "The March of the Young Builders of Socialism", dance "The Road the New Generation Is Taking",  dramatic witticism "No End", male chorus "For the Only One Country", and other colorful numbers.
 The performance ended with choral recitation and song "The Torch of Revolution" which reflects the firm pledge of the 8 million youth and children to staunchly advance along the road of the revolutionary cause of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was appreciated by the participants in the celebrations of the 60th anniversary of the youth league and members of the delegation of Korean youths and students in Japan and the delegation of the Youth Federation of Korean Nationals in China.

Anniversary of Death of Mun Ik Hwan Commemorated in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- Functions were reportedly held in south Korea to commemorate the 12th anniversary of the death of Rev. Mun Ik Hwan.
 A memorial service took place in Namyangju City, Kyonggi Province, on Jan. 14 with the attendance of members of the bereaved family of the deceased, members of civic and public organizations and public figures. Speakers said that Rev. Mun crossed the barrier of division and paved the way for reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A lecture was given on Jan. 15 under the sponsorship of the Late Spring Commemoration Council of the Late Mun Ik Hwan for Embracing National Reunification in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Poet Ko Un in a lecture on the subject of "Mun Ik Hwan and Reunification" said that Mun had the seed of the reunification movement rooted in our society at a time when words of "reunification" were prohibited owing to the assertion of frantic south-north confrontation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rev. Mun Ik Hwan practiced the reunification movement and shaped the way of reunification, providing the foundation of inter-Korean exchange, he added.

Great Alliance against Conservatives Called for in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- To achieve a great alliance against conservatives provides a basic way of meeting the blatant challenge of the pro-U.S. conservative forces, foiling their obstructive moves, steadily promoting progressive reforms and placing the movement for national reunification on a new higher stage in south Korea.
 Rodong Sinmun today observes this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the fact that the ultra-right conservative forces including the Grand National Party of south Korea are making desperate efforts to bring back the old era characterized by flunkeyism and treachery, fascism and inter-Korean confrontation, the article says:
 It is a very important socio-political and historical task for hewing out the destiny of the popular masses for independence to promote social progress and reforms and reenergize the movement for national reunification in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to frustrate the vicious obstructive moves of the reactionaries of history and achieve democracy and reunification, the popular masses should hold high the banner of unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These reactionaries are bound to make desperate efforts when they find themselves in an abyss of ruin. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The pro-U.S conservative forces are standing in the way of the cause of the fellow countrymen including the south Koreans to achieve independence, extending their tentacles not only to the political circle but to judicature, prosecution, media and other fields exercising their influence upon them. This shows how arduous the struggle of the south Korean people for democracy and national reunification is. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to frustrate the reactionary offensive of the pro-U.S. conservative forces, not only the broad popular masses but progressive pro-reform and pro-reunification political parties, politicians and organizations and figures of various strata should firmly unite as one under the uplifted banner of unity to ensure the undisputed superiority of the progressive forces to the reactionary conservative forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Various political parties and organizations in south Korea aspiring after progress, reform and national reunification should achieve the great unity of the progressive forces irrespective of ideology and ideal, placing the common interests of the nation and people above anything else and transcending the difference in ideals and party groupings.

Key Industries Updated 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- Many efforts have been directed to reconstructing and modernizing key industries in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. 
 Workers in the power, metal, engineering and other key industries are updating production processes while constructing new production centres on the basis of latest scientific and technological successes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those of the power industry have set a goal to put the production and management activities of the power stations throughout the country on a higher level.
 The electric power systems have been divided according to the local and production features and projects for introducing a new electric supply system are being pushed ahead as a nation-wide campaign. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The metal industry, too, is building new production bases and is updating equipment to further enhance the Juche character of the industry.
 The workers of the September General Iron Works have constructed an iron production base depending on local resources by introducing modern scientific technical achievements, thus remarkably increasing iron and steel production. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A 100-ton electric furnace has been built at the Hwanghae Iron and Steel Complex and metallurgical facilities are being improved at the Kim Chaek Iron and Steel Complex. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Workers of the engineering industry are registering successes in solving difficult scientific and technical problems arising in checking the efficiency of machine tools and heat treatment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Positive efforts are being made at the Huichon Machine Tool Factory to complete the unique machine tool control system and the assembling process of the main axis of machine tools on a high level.

New Year Performance, Masterpiece of Juche-oriented Art
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- The New Year celebration performance "Blue Sky over My Country" is going on at Pyongyang Indoor Stadium before  full house, giving confidence and courage to the army and people of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea who have turned out in the general advance of the Songun revolution this year.
 The performance, with a famous song "Blue Sky over My Country" loved by the Korean people as the seed, shows in an epical picture the firm will of the army and people to defend forever the blue sky over their country founded by President Kim Il Sung, under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il.
 Perfect in ideological content and artistic value are all the numbers of the performance including mixed duet and chorus "Blue Sky over My Country", chorus "Song to Marshal Kim Il Sung" and "Road of Victory" and female solo and chorus "Song to Comrade Kim Jong Il". It constitutes a new development of the Juche-oriented art. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The grand concert-style performance is given with 60 meter-wide chorus as the main. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance is staged to the accompaniment of chorus from the prelude to the finale. It is well combined with colorful songs and instrumental ensembles including vocal solo, vocal quartet, trumpet duet, violin ensemble and song to musical instrument. A group sculpture dance brings the ideological content of songs in bolder relief. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The unique gentle and elegant timbre strong in national coloring of the Korean-style mixed orchestra fully reflects ever efflorescing musical art of the country.
 The kayagum ensemble and male chorus "Song of Mt. Maebong" and oungum ensemble and pangchang "Always with the Guiding Star" to the accompaniment of the mixed orchestra which keeps the inherent playing technique of national musical instruments alive, are loudly applauded by the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The grand army-people chorus is participated by creators and artistes from the State Merited Chorus of the Korean People's Army, the Mansudae Art Troupe, the KPA Song and Dance Ensemble, the Phibada Opera Troupe and other famous art organizations of the army and society.
 The performance vividly reflects the ardent love of the army and people for the fatherland with the help of perfect ensemble, high artistic technique and new stage effect. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the performers are more than 200 international concours winners, "February 16 Art Prize" winners, People's and Merited Artistes, People's and Merited actors and actresses including Kim Ki Yong, Hong Kyong Hun, Ri Song Chol, Jo Hye Gyong, Ri Chon Ryong. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The New Year celebration performance, one more monumental masterpiece in the Songun era, thoroughly embodies the ideas and theories of Kim Jong Il, a great master in literature and art, from its repertoire to conduct, musical arrangement, playing and stage change.

Greetings to African Union Summit
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 19 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, sent a message of greetings to the Sixth Summit of the African Union on Jan. 18.
 The message said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I, in the name of the government of the DPRK, extend warm congratulations and cordial greetings to the heads of state and government and all other delegates to  the Sixth Summit of the African Union to be held in Khartoum amidst the keen interest and expectation of all the African people and the international community. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The African Union has made big progress in its efforts to realize independent development and integration of Africa and ensure regional peace and stability while rapidly enhancing its function and role after its foundation. It has put forward major proposals for the establishment of righteous and fair international relations including the UN reform and made good achievements for their realization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK government and people highly appreciate this   and extend full support and solidarity to the governments and people of the member nations of the African Union in their just cause to build independent and prosperous new Africa. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Convinced that the summit will mark an epochal occasion in taking measures for settling disputes and other regional issues by the concerted efforts of all the member nations, stepping up political and economic integration of the continent and developing the education and culture of Africa on a new level, I wholeheartedly hope that it would successfully discuss all the issues on the agenda as desired and demanded by all member nations and bear good fruition.
